                            <comment id="17566" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 11 May 2006 23:35:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out - indeed, those should be synchronized, at least in AbstractRefreshableApplicationContext.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason why this hasn&apos;t been noticed before is that such refreshing is hardly ever used in production. It&apos;s mainly intended as a development feature. Almost all Spring applications just reload at the overall application level, not on a per-application-context basis.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
